# Component contract

- Inspect neighboring source and specs before changing behavior.
- Preserve public inputs, model inputs, outputs, defaults, and form semantics.
- Keep component state signal-based and derived state in `computed()`.
- Keep side effects explicit, lifecycle-safe, and cleaned up on destroy.
- Preserve OnPush compatibility and avoid manual change detection workarounds.
- Keep template logic shallow and move complex transformations to TypeScript.
- Treat accessibility and error rendering as part of the public behavior.
- Update both READMEs when a public component API changes.
